<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="shall-modal-v">shall <strong><em>modal v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʃəl;ʃæl/    美 /ʃəl;ʃæl/  </p>
<p>[过去式should; shall not可缩写成shan’t]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[用于第一人称] 将要；将会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Shall we get off at the next stop?
我们下一站下车吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I shall be twenty next month.
下个月我就20岁了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>[表示说话者的允诺、命令、决心等，用于陈述句的第二、三人称] 必须；应；可：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You shall get the answer right this afternoon.
今天下午你一定会得到答复的。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[在问句中表示征求对方意见，主要用于第一、三人称] ...好吗：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Shall I fetch some chalk?
我去拿些粉笔来好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Shall he come to see you?
要他来见你吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>[用在表示意图、要求等的从句中] 应该；要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wish that you shall stay at home tonight.
我希望你今晚留在家里。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ordinary people merely think how they shall spend their time; a man of talent tries to use it.
普通人只想到要如何度过时间，而有才能的人却设法利用时间。——叔本华</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>[用于法律、条约、协定等文件中] 义务；规定：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Each citizen shall carry his identification card when travelling.
旅行时每个公民都必须带上身份证。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>One of our rules is that every student <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ wear school uniform while at school.  （2012 辽宁）<br />
A.might <br />
B.could <br />
C.shall <br />
D.will  </li>
<li>— Will you read me a story, Mummy?
— OK. You <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ have one if you go to bed as soon as possible.  （2011 陕西）<br />
A.might <br />
B.must <br />
C.could <br />
D.shall  </li>
<li>— What does the sign over there read?
— “No person <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ smoke or carry a lighted cigarette, cigar or pipe in this area.”  （2007 四川）<br />
A.will <br />
B.may <br />
C.shall <br />
D.must  </li>
<li>— What’s the name?
— Khulaifi. <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ I spell that for you?  （2006 北京）<br />
A.Shall <br />
B.Would <br />
C.Can <br />
D.Might  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. C  2. D  3. C  4. A  </p></div>